    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.8.0-dev-848-g36acb803c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, VIM8.1\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nUbuntu 20.04\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ngnome-terminal 3.36.2\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nRepo\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\nnvim --headless --listen 127.0.0.1:12346 --clean\r\nnvim-qt --server 127.0.0.1:12346\r\n:set guicursor=n-v-c:block-Cursor/lCursor,i-ci-ve:ver25-Cursor2/lCursor2,r-cr:hor20,o:hor50\r\n:highlight Cursor guibg=#ff007f\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nCursor color should change to pink.  This seems to be related to the fact that ui_ext[kUILinegrid] is not set when calling remote_ui_hl_attr_define() in src/nvim/api/ui.c.  If I comment that portion of code out the cursor is the correct color.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/21166472/184566725-8405e7a0-0654-4f64-96fe-908b327f0ac5.png)\r\n\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nCursor color stays white.",
